record.title: ADJOURNMENT UNTIL 10 A.M. TOMORROW
record.narrative:
ADJOURNMENT UNTIL 10 A.M. TOMORROW -- (Senate - October 22, 2007)

[Page: S13203]

speaking.paragraph: Madam President, if there is no further business, I ask unanimous consent that the Senate stand adjourned under the previous order.

record.narrative: There being no objection, the Senate at 8:21 p.m., adjourned until Tuesday, October 23, 2007, at 10 a.m.
